.title Help: Tcl Runtime Support
ABOUT THIS PACKAGE
The tclrun package installs the files necessary to run
Tcl (TclX).
Tcl is a simple scripting language for for controlling
and extending applications; its name stands for "tool
command language".  Tcl provides generic programming
facilities such as variables, loops and procedures, that
are useful for a variety of applications.
Futhermore Tcl is embeddable.  Its interpreter is a
library of C procedures that can easily be incorporated
into applications and each application can extend
the core Tcl features with additional commands for
that application.  To do this extension of commands
the "tcldev" package should be installed.


EXITING THE PACKAGE SELECTION MENU
Press <Enter> to enter your selections and to return to the
Install Menu.

EXITING HELP
Press <Esc> to return to the Package Selection menu.
Press <F1> for more help.
